    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<h2><em>jsoup</em></h2>\n<p>Self plug: I have just released a new Java HTML parser: <a href=\"http://jsoup.org/\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">jsoup</a>. I mention it here because I think it will do what you are after.</p>\n<p>Its party trick is a CSS selector syntax to find elements, e.g.:</p>\n<pre><code>String html = &quot;&lt;html&gt;&lt;head&gt;&lt;title&gt;First parse&lt;/title&gt;&lt;/head&gt;&quot;\n  + &quot;&lt;body&gt;&lt;p&gt;Parsed HTML into a doc.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/body&gt;&lt;/html&gt;&quot;;\nDocument doc = Jsoup.parse(html);\nElements links = doc.select(&quot;a&quot;);\nElement head = doc.select(&quot;head&quot;).first();\n</code></pre>\n<p>See the <a href=\"http://jsoup.org/apidocs/org/jsoup/select/Selector.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">Selector</a> javadoc for more info.</p>\n<p>This is a new project, so any ideas for improvement are very welcome!</p>\n"
  } ],
